{"word":"πάροικος","slug":"πάροικος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>πάροικος</b></el> <el>(πάρ-οικος, ον,) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>dwelling beside</i> or <i>near</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>; <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>:—<a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a> <i>a neighbour</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristotle'>Arist.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><el>πάροικος πόλεμος</el> a war <i>with neighbours</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>as <a href='S:Substantive'>Subst.</a> <i>a sojourner, alien</i>, <b><a href='S:New Testament'>NTest.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}